UNTIL Terminator of DO...UNTIL loop U.This statement is part of the DO..UNTIL repetitive loop. UNTIL takes a <testable expression> and will return control to the character after `DO if this is zero (false), otherwise execution will continue with the next statement. Examples:DO PRINT"O";UNTIL O; REM do foreverDO PRINT"$"; UNTIL COUNT=20; PRINT'####################DO INPUT"Calculation "A; PRINT"Answer is "A'; UNTIL A=12345678Calulation ?2*3Answer is 6Calculation ?AAnswer is 6Calculation ?12345678Answer is 12345678